          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Protons generated and accelerated to 200 MeV in the",
                "BNL LINAC were injected into the Booster accelerator",
                "and brought to the desired energies of 0.84, 1.00,",
                "and 1.42 GeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE",
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four HPGe detectors and associated",
                "electronics each interfaced to a PC-based MCA system.",
                "NaI(Tl) were used for beam monitoring."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The activation of spallation targets of",
                "Pb and W has been studied for range-thick targets at",
                "proton energies of 0.84, 1.00, and 1.42 GeV. The",
                "published in Table II data for irradiations #3,9 are",
                "for 1 GeV. The production of radioactive nuclei per",
                "incident proton per cubic centimetre has been",
                "determined at six depths in the target material."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Table II production yield values were modified by",
                "compiler using the recipe of C.E. Laird: Figures 16a,",
                "16b, etc. show that the results have units of",
                "nuclei/(proton*cm**3). These units were chosen to",
                "conform to the code calculations. To the best of my",
                "recollection, the volume in question was a circle of",
                "radius of 5 cm with the thickness of the foils(.021",
                "cm for Pb and .014 cm for W). This was the volume of",
                "the foils in the larger target, so we assume no",
                "activation outside the target assembly. So, to get",
                "nuclei per proton, you should multiply by the volume",
                "of the foils! Consequently, the calculated target",
                "volumes for Pb and W are 1.6493 cm**3 and 1.0995",
                "cm**3, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Point-source efficiencies do not properly account for",
                "all efficiency and attenuation effects associated",
                "with the activation of extended samples by a broad",
                "beam of activating particles. These calculated",
                "corrections were used in conjunction with the",
                "point-source efficiencies to obtain the absolute",
                "activity of the W and Pb foils. The associated",
                "uncertainty was included in the total activation",
                "uncertainty for these foils. An associated uncertainty",
                "of 30% of the correction (a correction of 7% was",
                "assigned an error of 2.1%, or 30% of 7%) was assigned",
                "with each correction."
              ]
            }
          ],
